  "articleSummary": "**Summary**\n\n\"Into the Breach\" is a technical analysis and defensive guide addressing the evolving landscape of developer-targeted supply chain attacks and credential theft. The article argues that modern developer environments have become \"credential warehouses\" where traditional \"be careful\" advice fails; instead, security must be enforced through structural boundaries and isolation. Intended for software engineers and DevOps professionals, the text advocates for specific technical mitigations including the use of DevContainers for filesystem isolation, the deployment of Canarytokens as digital tripwires, and the implementation of package release delays. The tone is urgent yet pragmatic, framing the developer's local machine as a high-stakes attack surface that requires proactive, automated defense-in-depth rather than human vigilance.",
